                "text": "Whenever a creature targets the hound with a <a aonid=\"106\" game-obj=\"Traits\">mental</a> effect,"
            },
            {
                "type": "stat_block_section",
                "subtype": "ability",
                "ability_type": "automatic",
                "name": "Ripping Gaze",
                "text": "that creature takes 4d6 mental damage (DC 25 basic Will save). On a critical failure, it<br/>also becomes <a aonid=\"5\" game-obj=\"Conditions\">confused</a> for 1d4 rounds.<br/> (<a aonid=\"206\" game-obj=\"Traits\">aura</a>, <a aonid=\"65\" game-obj=\"Traits\">evocation</a>, <a aonid=\"120\" game-obj=\"Traits\">occult</a>, <a aonid=\"163\" game-obj=\"Traits\">visual</a>) 30 feet. The hound of Tindalos's eyes glow balefully, causing painful but bloodless wounds to rip open in the body of a creature that meets its awful gaze. When a creature ends its turn in the aura's emanation, it takes 4d6 slashing damage (DC 25 basic Fortitude save). A creature that critically succeeds at its save is temporarily immune for 24 hours."
            },
            {
                "type": "stat_block_section",
                "subtype": "ability",
                "ability_type": "automatic",
                "name": "Vulnerable to Curved Space",
                "text": "When a hound of Tindalos is not adjacent to a structural angle of 90\u00ba (or more acute), its resistance to physical damage is suppressed and it becomes <a aonid=\"34\" game-obj=\"Conditions\">sickened 1</a>. It can't recover from this sickened condition, but the condition ends automatically once the hound is again adjacent to a suitable angle."
            }
